<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Block vs Inline Elements</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>Block Elements (div)</h2>
    <div style="border:1px solid blue;">Div Element 1</div>
    <div style="border:1px solid blue;">Div Element 2</div>
    <div style="border:1px solid blue;">Div Element 3</div>
    <h2>Inline Elements (span)</h2>
    <span style="border:1px solid blue;">Span 1</span>
    <span style="border:1px solid blue;">Span 2</span>
    <span style="border:1px solid blue;">Span 3</span>
    <h2>Observations</h2>
    <p>
        1. div is a block-level element. Each div starts on a new line .
    </p>
    <p>
        2. span is an inline element. Multiple span elements appear on the same line.
    </p>
    <p>
        3. div is mainly used for creating sections or layouts.
    </p>
    <p>
        4. span is mainly used for styling or grouping small portions of text.
    </p>
</body>
</html>
